How to Create Building Models in Simscape

Table of Contents
Create Building using Utilities Import Building Information Models Create Building using Libraries
In this workflow, rooms and apartments create the building models, as shown in the picture below. A room is the smallest unit, multiple rooms combine to form an apartment, and multiple apartments combine to form a floor plan. A floor plan extruded in the vertical direction creates a building composed of the specified number of floors. To make these models, use utilities like addRoomToFloorPlan, defineSingleApartmentUnit, and generateBuilding3Dlayout. To learn more about such utilities, see Function Reference List.
You can also choose to import your own Building Information Model (BIM) into Simscape. Simscape provides utilities that read a BIM file and create a building automatically. You can also choose to create building from basic building blocks or libraries provided in the project directory (Components/Library).
To summarize, there are three ways to create a building, as described in the three workflows or Live Scripts in the Workflow folder.
  1. Create Building using Utilities
  2. Import Building Information Model BIM into Simscape
  3. Create Building using Libraries

Create Building using Utilities

To learn how to create buildings quickly using utilities, see Create Building Model with Solar Loads (Workflow/CreateBuildingModelWithSolarLoad.mlx). In this workflow, you learn how to define rooms, create apartments, and construct a 3D building. At the end of the workflow, you can save your building definition in a XML part and use it later or share with others. To open and run the workflow, enter at the MATLAB command prompt.
edit CreateBuildingModelWithSolarLoad.mlx

Import Building Information Models

To learn how to import Building Information Model (BIM) data into Simscape, see Import Building Information Model for Heat Load Analysis (Workflow/ImportBIMforHeatLoadAnalysis.mlx). You will learn how to use utilities to import the BIM model, check the imported data, and setup the model for analysis. To open and run the workflow, enter at the MATLAB command prompt.
edit ImportBIMforHeatLoadAnalysis.mlx

Create Building using Libraries

If you do not wish to use Building custom component for your work and create something from the basic building blocks, then you can make use of Components/Libraries provided in the project. The custom componets like Ambient and Building leverage the same libraries and you have the option to construct your building from the basic building blocks. To learn how to create buildings using custom Simscape Building libraries, see Build Detailed House Using Custom Library Components (Workflow/DetailedHouseModelUsingCustomLib.mlx). In this workflow, you will learn how to create a single detailed room model using the custom library blocks provided in the Simulink Library Browser. To open and run the workflow, enter at the MATLAB command prompt.
edit DetailedHouseModelUsingCustomLib.mlx
